<font color="#FF0000">FAVORITE SONS</font><br>
<tt>Mon Feb 23  5:47:53 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
<br>
You have all so boldly blessed us all with your raw emotions on these pages. Your tears, anger, humor and gentleness have been rare gifts of your souls, allowing us to know each of you more intimately than most people we have known a lifetime.  <br><br>
I am so grateful that each of you have expressed that this forum has given you the opportunity to unravel so much that has been tangled up and unexamined for years and I pray that which was once a nightmare becomes only a rich reservoir from which you &quot;choose&quot; to drink - rejoicing in and sharing the great wisdom and reverence for life that is ultimately offered by such an experience.<br><br>
To all Vietnam Veterans, whether you were volunteers or drafted, stalwart or terrified, proud or ashamed of your experiences, it is time to come home - truly home - from this long, dark road most of you have been travelling alone for so many years.  Open your eyes and hearts and you will find many, many who love you and are grateful for your sacrifice.<br><br>
You are indeed our &quot;favorite sons&quot; - please forgive us for taking so long to wake up and properly embrace you. <br><br>
WELCOME HOME!  May the rest of your journey be with joy, gratitude and a forgiving heart - God knows, you've earned it!    <br>

<p><code>--   (AN OLD FRIEND) </code><p>


